### STEP 1 — src/ipc.ts
### Add `sendFile` to IpcDeps and handle `type: 'file_upload'` messages

In the IpcDeps interface (around line 14), add:

```typescript
sendFile?: (jid: string, filePath: string, caption?: string) => Promise<void>;
```

After the existing `type === 'message'` block (around line 84), add:

```typescript
} else if (data.type === 'file_upload' && data.chatJid && data.filePath) {
  // Security: only allow files within /workspace/ipc/ or /tmp/
  const allowedPrefixes = ['/workspace/ipc/', '/tmp/'];
  const isAllowed = allowedPrefixes.some((p) => (data.filePath as string).startsWith(p));
  if (!isAllowed) {
    logger.warn({ filePath: data.filePath, sourceGroup }, 'File upload rejected: path outside allowed dirs');
  } else if (deps.sendFile) {
    await deps.sendFile(data.chatJid, data.filePath as string, data.caption as string | undefined);
    logger.info({ chatJid: data.chatJid, filePath: data.filePath }, 'File uploaded to Slack via IPC');
  } else {
    logger.warn({ sourceGroup }, 'file_upload IPC message received but sendFile not implemented');
  }
```

